# Cline Rules for SHML Platform
# These instructions are automatically injected into every Cline conversation.

## Context
- This is the SHML Platform workspace (ML/AI platform with RAY, MLflow, monitoring)
- Local LLM: Qwen3.5-27B-Q4_K_M running via llama.cpp on RTX 3090 Ti
- API endpoint: http://localhost:8000/v1

## Code Standards
- Prefer Python 3.10+ type hints and async/await patterns
- Follow existing project structure and naming conventions
- Use descriptive variable names; avoid single-letter names except loop indices
- Always include error handling and logging

## Infrastructure
- Docker Compose services in shml-platform/
- MLflow tracking at http://localhost:5000
- Ray cluster dashboard at http://localhost:8265
- Monitoring (Grafana) at http://localhost:3000

## Behavior
- Before making changes, read relevant files to understand context
- Make targeted, minimal changes unless refactoring is explicitly requested
- Explain non-obvious decisions with inline comments
- Run status checks before assuming services are up or down
